  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p>\n<p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p>\n<p>Skim through these steps</p>\n<p>Wash your fruit and veg</p>\n<p>Note: equipment and pan sizes vary. Ensure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 mins)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-tuna-lemon-and-caper-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now let's get started!</strong></p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>spring onions </strong>roughly (chop them in one bunch for speed!)</p>\n<p>Chop the<strong> basil</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-tuna-lemon-and-caper-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>half</strong> of t</span>he <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> until you have a pile of shavings <span class=\"text-highlight\">(set these aside for serving!)</span></p>\n<p>Grate the <strong>remaining Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-tuna-lemon-and-caper-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>quick cook spaghetti</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook the<strong> spaghetti</strong> for just 2 min or until cooked with a slight bite (it will keep cooking in the sauce later!)</p>\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>spaghetti</strong> reserving a large cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-tuna-lemon-and-caper-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, drain the <strong>tuna</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>capers</strong>, <strong>roasted </strong><strong>garlic paste</strong> and <strong>drained tuna</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 sec</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-tuna-lemon-and-caper-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained spaghetti</strong> with the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>juice</strong></span> of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong>, the<strong> grated cheese</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Add a splash of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>\n<p>Cook for 30 sec further or until the sauce beings to stick to the pasta</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-tuna-lemon-and-caper-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the pan from the heat and stir through the<strong> chopped basil</strong> – this is your <strong>tuna, lemon &amp; caper spaghetti </strong></p>\n<p>Cut the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>remaining</strong></span> <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-tuna-lemon-and-caper-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Set the<strong> tuna, lemon &amp; <span class=\"text-highlight\">caper</span> spaghetti</strong> in the centre of the table, ready to share</p>\n<p>Garnish with the<strong> lemon wedges</strong>,<strong> rocket</strong> and <strong>cheese shavings</strong> and let everyone dig in</p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
